metadata.name: Votux
metadata.description:
"Î¼m" (Micrometer) introduces Yoshi Sodeoka's recent visual research into life-forms blossoming and mutating in condensed microscopic systems.

In this new collection, photo-luminescent corpuscles generate and grow as they drift suspended, buoyant in fluid darkness flecked with tiny, glowing particles.

Hints of vertebrate spinal development flicker and fade as if the first sensory nervous system is about to emerge, evolving toward awareness.
